  "body": "See: http://www.cs.bu.edu/~goldbe/projects/eclipseEth\r\n\r\n### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nWe should build in some basic protections against eclipse attacks.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\n- Require that a certain percentage of the peer connections are initiated as outgoing connection requests.\r\n    - Configuration parameter that sets required number of connections that originate from a dial-out connection\r\n    - Configuration parameter that sets the ratio of allowed dial-in to dial-out connections.\r\n- Ensure that the IP addresses for peer connections are not all to the same IP address.\r\n    - Configuration parameter that sets the maximum number of connections to a single IP address that are allowed, default to something like 3.\r\n",
